= Evidence Lifecycle V2 =

{{info}}
**Target Evidence Reference** - This page replaces V1 evidence-quality-filter thinking with the V2 evidence lifecycle: query planning, acquisition, applicability, extraction, sufficiency, and evidence transparency.

The current V1 Evidence Quality Filtering page remains runtime documentation until V2 cutover.
{{/info}}

== Purpose ==

V2 treats evidence as a lifecycle, not as a late deterministic cleanup pass. The evidence stage must build a source-backed, multilingual, topic-neutral corpus that can support evidence-emergent ClaimAssessmentBoundaries and evidence-cited verdicts.

== Lifecycle Flow ==

{{mermaid}}
flowchart TB
  CC["ClaimContract\nselected AtomicClaims"] --> QP["Query plan\nLLM semantic planning"]
  QP --> SEARCH["Search providers\nstructural provider calls"]
  SEARCH --> FETCH["Source fetch and extraction\nstatus, retries, trace"]
  FETCH --> APP["Relevance and applicability\nLLM judgment"]
  APP --> EXTRACT["Evidence extraction\nEvidenceItem + EvidenceScope"]
  EXTRACT --> SR["Source reliability signal\nLLM-owned where semantic;\ncached and versioned"]
  EXTRACT --> EC["EvidenceCorpus"]
  SR --> EC
  EC --> SUFF["SufficiencyAssessment\ncontinue, refine, caveat, damage"]
  SUFF --> BS["BoundarySet input"]

  WARN["Warning policy"] --> FETCH
  WARN --> SUFF

  classDef semantic fill:#e8f4ff,stroke:#2463a7,color:#08233d
  classDef structural fill:#edf7ed,stroke:#3d8b40,color:#102a12
  classDef gate fill:#fff4d6,stroke:#9a6700,color:#3a2600
  class QP,APP,EXTRACT,SR semantic
  class SEARCH,FETCH,EC structural
  class SUFF,WARN gate
{{/mermaid}}

== Stage Responsibilities ==

|= Step |= Semantic owner |= Structural owner |= Output
| Query planning | LLM proposes search intent for selected AtomicClaims and possible evidence dimensions. | Prompt/model gateway validates variables, model policy, cache dimensions, and budget. | QueryPlan
| Source acquisition | Search strings are provider-facing; provider ranking is not treated as verdict truth. | Provider calls, retries, rate limits, fetch status, source IDs, trace events. | SourceCandidate list
| Applicability | LLM decides whether a source or excerpt is relevant and applicable to the claim and evidence need. | URL/source identity, fetch status, content availability, dedupe by structural identity. | ApplicabilityResult
| Evidence extraction | LLM extracts EvidenceItems, EvidenceScopes, claim direction, probativeValue, and source-type rationale. | Schema validation, stable IDs, citation/source reference checks. | EvidenceItem list
| Sufficiency | LLM-owned where adequacy is semantic; policy records continue/refine/caveat/damage. | Gate status, warning events, missing-dimension list, run ledger entry. | SufficiencyAssessment

== EvidenceCorpus Contract ==

The EvidenceCorpus should contain:

* selected AtomicClaim IDs it was built for;
* source records with provider, fetch status, source identity, and retrieval trace;
* EvidenceItems with source reference, statement, category, claimDirection, EvidenceScope, probativeValue, and sourceType;
* source reliability signals when available;
* applicability and extraction decisions with model/prompt/config trace;
* warnings and scarcity indicators classified by the shared warning policy;
* structural validation status for citations, source references, and schema integrity.

== Quality Boundary ==

V2 allows deterministic structural checks, but not deterministic semantic evidence decisions.

|= Allowed deterministic checks |= Must be LLM-owned or approved semantic policy
| Empty/null input, schema validation, source URL presence, source ID consistency, citation ID matching, fetch status, duplicate source identity, budget accounting | Relevance, applicability, probative value, source meaning, claim direction, EvidenceScope compatibility, evidence strength, multilingual semantic equivalence

== Rejected V1 Carry-Forward ==

The following V1 evidence-quality-filter mechanisms are not V2 target design:

* vague phrase counts;
* keyword or regex evidence classification;
* Jaccard/text-overlap semantic dedupe;
* language-specific wording rules;
* deterministic category-specific meaning requirements;
* late silent dropping of evidence without traceable warning/gate state.

If V2 needs an evidence-quality rule that affects meaning, it must be modeled as an LLM task or an approved configurable semantic policy, with caching and validation.

== Warning And Scarcity Handling ==

Evidence scarcity is an analytical reality, not automatically a system error. V2 must distinguish:

* recovered routine provider issues: silent or admin-only;
* partial acquisition degradation that materially limits evidence: user-visible warning;
* source scarcity or inaccessible evidence: caveat or UNVERIFIED path depending on sufficiency;
* system failure that prevents trustworthy analysis: damaged/non-analytical result.

== Multilingual Requirement ==

Evidence lifecycle behavior must work across languages. V2 may preserve original-language source material and must not force translation as a prerequisite unless an approved stage contract requires it. Semantic applicability, extraction, and scope compatibility remain LLM-owned.

